"{\"id\":{\"0\":\"c0\",\"1\":\"c1\"},\"class\":{\"0\":\"considered\",\"1\":\"considered\"},\"tocase\":{\"0\":\"Colgate-Palmolive Co & Anor v Cussons Pty Ltd [1993] FCA 536 ; (1993) 118 ALR 248\",\"1\":\"Bhagat v Global Custodians Ltd [2002] FCA 223\"},\"text\":{\"0\":\"2 The Respondents have submitted that costs ought to be ordered on an indemnity basis. They acknowledge that the ordering of costs on this basis is exceptional requiring some special or unusual feature: Colgate-Palmolive Co & Anor v Cussons Pty Ltd [1993] FCA 536 ; (1993) 118 ALR 248 at 257. They also acknowledge that there is a general reluctance to make an order for costs to be paid on an indemnity basis against the litigant in person: Bhagat v Global Custodians Ltd [2002] FCA 223 at [57] and [60] per O'Loughlin, Whitlam and Marshall JJ.\",\"1\":\"2 The Respondents have submitted that costs ought to be ordered on an indemnity basis. They acknowledge that the ordering of costs on this basis is exceptional requiring some special or unusual feature: Colgate-Palmolive Co & Anor v Cussons Pty Ltd [1993] FCA 536 ; (1993) 118 ALR 248 at 257. They also acknowledge that there is a general reluctance to make an order for costs to be paid on an indemnity basis against the litigant in person: Bhagat v Global Custodians Ltd [2002] FCA 223 at [57] and [60] per O'Loughlin, Whitlam and Marshall JJ.\"}}"